  "read": "The new TileLang panel-dense final fold is correct at S128 and lowers at S4096. It replaces the PyTorch index_add diagnostic with a no-atomic final reducer that owns one compressed group and D block, then sums compact partial rows across token tiles. This is a real TileLang final-output contract and trims fold-only time from about 0.119 ms to 0.0485 ms, but full-path latency only improves from 8.204 ms to 8.130 ms. So the retained TileLang branch is now compact query-major MFMA producer plus TileLang panel-dense final fold, while the next meaningful speed lever remains the producer: reduce or fuse the 128 MiB compact partial stream, or consume compact rows directly in compressor/LI backward."
